name: TheAtlantic
text: Welcome to the great wait. Here's how to not go crazy the week before an election. The latest Atlantic Daily, by @mimbsy: https://t.co/UdWnF7abqR

name: TheAtlantic
text: RT @YAppelbaum: Jesse Helms’s hometown—like countrypolitan places across the country—is changing. And unless the GOP changes with it, it’s in big trouble. @GrahamDavidA reports from Union Country, North Carolina: https://t.co/ztUUQpXzLc

name: TheAtlantic
text: Countrypolitan places "are distinct from rural areas, which are mostly Republican, and cities, which are heavily Democratic ... That makes them pivotal counties, in 2020 and in the future," writes @GrahamDavidA: https://t.co/lgifxcuNRD

name: TheAtlantic
text: In this week's "Dear Therapist," @LoriGottlieb1 advises a reader who worries that she and her boyfriend aren't on the same page. https://t.co/BbvMKeTVbq

name: TheAtlantic
text: Related: Earlier this month, @LoriGottlieb1 advised a reader whose boyfriend is jealous that she still values memories from her first marriage. https://t.co/HAt07KKmky

name: TheAtlantic
text: RT @GrahamDavidA: North Carolina could tip the presidential election and the Senate, and many people have looked to suburban NC to figure out how it might go: https://t.co/SLzWnKOwm9 (1/x)

name: TheAtlantic
text:
RT @JeffreyGoldberg: .@Yascha_Mounk: "Parts of the left now seek far-reaching censorship in social media... and are openly hostile to free speech. The likely future mayor of Portland, Oregon, has appeared to glorify mass murderers such as Che Guevara and Mao Zedong..."
https://t.co/17pO9QiGqd

name: TheAtlantic
text: "Voting for Trump to stem the rising tide of illiberalism is about as pure an example of cutting off your nose to spite your face as political life can afford," @Yascha_Mounk writes: https://t.co/41g4nhIF5l

name: TheAtlantic
text: Related: Many Americans trusted intuition to help guide them through this disaster, but it has led us astray. In September, @edyong209 detailed nine conceptual errors that are keeping the U.S. trapped in the pandemic: https://t.co/okhYDQgusi

name: TheAtlantic
text: America’s pandemic nightmare is a case study in how fear, confusion, and tribalism can put even well-meaning people in totally avoidable danger, writes @amandamull: https://t.co/OijvpWzQv4

name: TheAtlantic
text:
RT @marinakoren: The moon is fine. 

You know who's not fine? You. Me. Us. That's why people panicked over NASA's cryptic announcement. We can't handle surprises right now. https://t.co/bKkALXdq7C

name: TheAtlantic
text:
RT @emmaogreen: "I’ve always voted for what would benefit my family, as opposed to the general public. This time it was more like trying to...save the country, because I really think we’re in a bad place.” 
Read @GrahamDavidA on the changing map of North Carolina:
https://t.co/gWprXWjtiz

name: TheAtlantic
text: Compelling evidence suggests that Donald Trump’s "countless sins and defects are rooted in mental instability, pathological narcissism, and profound moral impairment." Read our endorsement of Joe Biden: https://t.co/EAl8jsmlhA
